  "response": "The IT job market in Canada is generally strong and offers good opportunities. Here are some key points:\n\n1. High Demand\n- Strong demand for skilled IT professionals\n- Shortage of qualified workers in many tech roles\n- Growing tech sectors in cities like Toronto, Vancouver, and Montreal\n\n2. Popular Job Roles\n- Software Developers\n- Cloud Computing Specialists\n- Cybersecurity Professionals\n- Data Scientists\n- AI and Machine Learning Engineers\n- Network Administrators\n\n3. Salary Ranges\n- Average IT salaries range from $60,000 to $120,000+ CAD\n- Senior roles and specialized skills can earn higher salaries\n- Competitive compensation compared to other industries\n\n4. Key Tech Hubs\n- Toronto: Largest tech job market\n- Vancouver: Strong tech and startup ecosystem\n- Montreal: Growing AI and software development scene\n- Calgary and Edmonton: Emerging tech markets\n\n5. Growth Factors\n- Digital transformation across industries\n- Government support for tech innovation\n- Increasing investment in technology\n- Growing startup ecosystem\n\n6. Immigration Opportunities\n- Canada has favorable immigration policies for skilled tech workers\n- Express Entry system prioritizes tech professionals\n- Provincial nominee programs support tech talent\n\nOverall, the Canadian IT job market is robust and offers promising career prospects.",
